wiki.summary: “ROCKSTAR” is a song recorded by LISA. This is the lead single from her debut full length studio album "ALTER EGO", released after almost three years of dormancy from her solo career. The style of the song is mixed with elements from hip-hop to electronic and showcases unique styles of both singing and production. The song involves producers Ryan Tedder and Sam Homaee, both known for making pop hits. Lyrically, the song is about Lisa’s wealth, skills, and her affluent life, consisting of fortune and success. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “ROCKSTAR” is a song recorded by LISA. This is the lead single from her debut full length studio album "ALTER EGO", released after almost three years of dormancy from her solo career. The style of the song is mixed with elements from hip-hop to electronic and showcases unique styles of both singing and production. The song involves producers Ryan Tedder and Sam Homaee, both known for making pop hits. Lyrically, the song is about Lisa’s wealth, skills, and her affluent life, consisting of fortune and success. Lisa also boasts about her talents such as influencing others, rapping, singing, and being bilingual. The music video compliments the rich, electro concept of the single, including cyberpunk scenery setting place in Bangkok, Chinatown and Yaowarat Road in Thailand. Most importantly, the film displays Lisa’s outstanding choreography and fashion throughout each scene. Read more on Last.fm.
